#: ../../post_processing/ocrtext_converter.rst:16
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "The OCR text converter is a tool to parse the contents of an image and "
#| "detect areas with text to convert into editable and translatable "
#| "characters files."
msgid ""
"The **OCR Text Converter** tool parses the contents of an image, detects "
"areas with text, and converts that text into editable and translatable "
"characters files."
msgstr ""
"Il convertitore di testo OCR è uno strumento per analizzare il contenuto di "
"un'immagine e individuare aree con testo da convertire in file con caratteri "
"modificabili e traducibili."

#: ../../post_processing/ocrtext_converter.rst:18
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "The tool can batch optical character recognition (OCR) over images, and "
#| "their translations in many languages using an online translator engine. "
#| "It also allows you to review the text and make corrections and offers "
#| "spell checking."
msgid ""
"The tool can perform batch optical character recognition (OCR) over images, "
"and produce translations in many languages using an online translator "
"engine. It also allows you to review the text with the aid of spell "
"checking, and make corrections as needed."
msgstr ""
"Lo strumento può eseguire in serie il riconoscimento ottico dei caratteri "
"(OCR) sulle immagini e la loro traduzione in molte lingue, utilizzando un "
"motore di traduzione in linea. Ti permette inoltre di revisionare il testo e "
"apportare le dovute correzioni, anche tramite correzione ortografica "
"incorporata."

#: ../../post_processing/ocrtext_converter.rst:20
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "The tool use in background the `Tesseract <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
#| "Tesseract_(software)>`_, a powerful open-source optical character "
#| "recognition engine available for Linux, macOS, and Windows."
msgid ""
"The tool uses the `Tesseract <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Tesseract_(software)>`_, a powerful open-source optical character "
"recognition engine available for Linux, macOS, and Windows."
msgstr ""
"Lo strumento usa in background il `Tesseract <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Tesseract_(software)>`_, un motore avanzato di riconoscimento ottico dei "
"caratteri disponibile per Linux, macOS e Windows."

